The paper presents a novel approach for unsupervised learning of disentangled and interpretable representations from sequential data. This involves exploiting the multi-scale nature of information in sequential data by formulating it explicitly within a factorized hierarchical graphical model that imposes sequence-dependent priors and sequence-independent priors to different sets of latent variables. This work involves machine learning, natural language processing, and speech processing, which are all covered by the above-listed sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.SD (Sound), cs.SI (Speech Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
